			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Personally, I don't agree with this. If you spend most of your time kiting, you're going to get hit pretty infrequently. At 32, Vard's defense was at 120 or so - 40 points off where it needed to be. That's a substantial lack of AC and would probably lead to creamed bard if I was tanking at any time in my 40s or 50s.
<br />

<br />
I went to CC and pulled orcs near the town to raise my skill. I was doing moderately well, but still dying or having to run back to the guards because a fight went badly (I was also training up my piercing, which was way off, too).
<br />

<br />
So, I got a cleric friend to come down and help me out. He was 53 and I would go pull three or four orcs at a time and just beat them down one by one while he healed me. With AE songs and slows I was able to hold agro the whole time. 
<br />

<br />
Now I'm 33 and my defense is 158, only 7 points off where it needs to be. I'll stay in CC until it's maxed and then go kite, but I'll make sure to tank down mobs at the beginning of each level to keep it up. It took several hours of the kind of beating I just described to get it to raise those 38 points.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />
Vard</span></td>
