				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi there,
<br />

<br />
My defense skill was always 50 points off. I had the hardest time raising it. I would get beat up pretty badly and yet no skill ups... at one point I thought I was capped due to level, even though I had 50 points to go according to the known formula 5 x level + 5 for skills cap, it sucked so much.
<br />

<br />
I wish I would have bound at Orc Lift in Gfay when I was level 9 and go attack orcs over and over till my defense was 50 at that time.
<br />

<br />
I very rarely tank, group always have designated tank. Just lately my defense has gone up on a more reasonable pace (at around 200 it has finally picked up, now at 225). Once, I was main tank on a LDoN adventure, and defense skill didn't go up a single point after one hour of tanking.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I still never get to tank, but use ripostes for training Defense Skill. LDoN has helped on the leveling of my defense skill. Hard to raise skill by taking ripostes off BoT giants, but if healer is cleric and no mana issues, you bet I will! 27 Skills points to max it, woot!! Every once in a while, you get groupmates glancing at you about tanking in front of mob, and an ocasionaly tell or 2 about it though, but LDoN mobs are so gimp, even druids don't get LOM so mostly they leave you alone about it.
<br />

<br />
I do agree with not stopping regular exping to practice defense skill off light blues. Use ripostes for skill ups, LDoN is good training camp. Being the puller 99% of the times helps too.
<br />

<br />
Current AC is 1275 with Virtue, 75 extra AC points pending on my Defense Skill being maxed, woot!
<br />

<br />
Nilufer. </span></td>
