				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Defense Skill<a name="22232"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 04 4:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Why is everyone so vehemently against kiting?  Sure, it's repetitive, and you don't get to BS much while you're doing it, but the XP gains are much greater, and what good bard really talks during a group except during downtime.
<br />

<br />
The only 2 arguments I have against kiting are 1) lack of defense and 2) knowledge of the character and game in general.  However, I've got #2 from previous characters, and #1 I'm still debating on.
<br />

<br />
The XP, however, completely wins against them.
<br />

<br />
Personally, this bard is my new main.  However, all of my friends are 65.  I'd much rather level this bard asap to get back in the raid with my friends than putz around w/ pickup groups in PC just to raise some defense.  Half of the people in PC are going to re-roll anyway, so why bother?  Pickup groups, especially at lower levels, are notorious for being more of a hassle than an enjoyable experience.  Clerics who nuke and go oom, necros who dot mezzed mobs, warriors who forget to turn on autoattack, and nothing you can do or say to help them tactfully.  Forget that, I'm soloing until people can generally be dependable.  
<br />

<br />
Furthermore, I know where some dependable people are - in my guild, at level 65.  I'm going to level, and do it fast, to get back up there with them.
<br />

<br />
But, that's my opinion.  If you want to grind out group xp, so be it...  Just why bitch about people who don't go that route?  Let me have my mobs, you keep your groups.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, /threadjack off
<br />

<br />
I tend to agree with jazz - at 65, if you get hit, you're in trouble anyway.  Defense isn't going to help that much - dodge will be much more useful.  Bards are a plate class, but we don't mitigate damage like a war.  How long do war's last against most 65+ mobs without having a CH rotation?  Whens the last time you saw a bard w/ a CH rotation vs. a 65 mob?
<br />

<br />
Your best bet?  Just don't get hit.  Where do you practice not getting hit?
<br />
&quot;F'N KITING&quot;
<br />

<br />
-- Front</span></td>
