				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Defense Skill<a name="22262"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 04 5:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I'm not a fan of PL - forces you into a debt of some sort and you'll likely be PLing someone else at some wierd time.  Besides, with a bard, we don't really need PL.  I got 6 levels in 3 and a half hours at 32 solo in TM.
<br />

<br />
But, I wouldn't bother w/ the druid pl just to check your stats - it's easy.  You have NONE.  You've got a lot of training points, some percussion, and a little bit of string, but that's it.  Luckily for us, we can use the training points for dodge and AFK train all of our instruments.  At higher levels, grouping, raising offense is easy. 
<br />

<br />
The only skill you'll lack in the end is defense, and thusly AC.
<br />

<br />
As far as raiding, though, I agree - you won't have much practice as a bard in a raid situation.  However, the hard thing about raiding is learning how to raid, not so much learning how to play a bard.  In learning how to raid, you sortof have to know what all of the other classes are going to be doing anyway.  Learn how to raid on one toon, and you only have to learn some ins and outs on another.
<br />

<br />
I don't think bards are very difficult to play from a logical point of view - you just need to know what songs to play and when.  The hard part is learning specific mechanics of a bard - twisting and general CC - but they just take a little getting used to and some adjusting.  
<br />

<br />
By the time you get your first char up past 50, you've likely learned a lot about the game.  My old main is 65, so I feel confident about his part in a raid.  Also, a close friend of mine is a bard, and he and I have talked at length about barding, and after the practice I've got from 1-50 (56 now, working on some AA's), I feel confident about my place in a raid.
<br />

<br />
But, that's not for everyone.  You kite to 50 in 2 weeks on your first char, you've still got plenty to learn, and I don't recommend it.  But if you're re-rolling on a new server or rolling an alt to get back to the endgame, then kiting is the way to go.
<br />

<br />
Just need to raise that defense so I don't feel so gimp, lol.</span></td>
